2. CALCULATION PHASE
--------------------------------------------------

Facility Availability (FA)
--------------------------
Facility Availability is calculated hierarchically:

The calculation processes each 10-minute interval in the current billing period:

**Per-Interval Processing:**
   
   This snapshot is appended to the historical inverter availability deque.


5. Calculate Facility Availability (FA)
   FA is the average of all weighted availabilities across the current billing period:

The historical deque grows continuously as new intervals are processed, maintaining
the complete record while allowing efficient extraction of the rolling 30-day window.

**Per-Interval Processing:**

1. Extract Rolling 7-Day Window
   The system retrieves the most recent 7 no-event days from the complete historical
   deque of no-event days.

4. Update No-Event Days History
   At the end of each day (last interval at 23:50), if the day had no PREPA events:
   - Calculate daily totals (NEO, GK)
   - Append the day's data to the complete historical deque
   




